Description: I’m putting up for sale 5 of my Ibanez guitars. Check my other listings or the last picture. I got a little bit carried away with the gear acquisitions, so now will have to sell the ones that I don’t play. This listing is for Ibanez RGR421EXFM in blackberry sunburst. It’s in nearly brand new condition, there is some discoloration on the hardware due to age, and a few scuffs that I can’t even pick up on camera. Played it a few times and put in the gig bag to store. I just have way too many guitars. I recently put the fresh set of strings, polished the frets, and conditioned the finger board. Feels and plays like new. It has beautiful flamed maple top, designed by EMG pick ups, Wizard II neck, reversed headstock, made in Indonesia. Here’s some info from web: The RGR421EXFM is an RG series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 2007. The RGR421EXFM features a mahogany body with flamed maple top bolted to a maple Wizard II neck with reverse headstock and 24-fret bound rosewood fingerboard with dot position markers. Components include dual humbucking pickups and a standard hard-tail bridge. It was originally introduced with Designed by EMG pickups. After those were discontinued in 2008 US only. Will ship within 2 days of receiving payment. There are two shipping options and free local pick up if you are in NYC area.
Title: Ibanez RGR421EXFM RG Series Electric Guitar Designed By EMG Wizard II Reversed
